The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Rulebook for Kali puja
                                                                                                               Rulebook for Kali puja
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Calcutta police have issued a leaflet with the dos and donts for Kali puja organisers in the city. Kali puja is on October 17 and the idols should be immersed on October 20.         
	Do: Organisers should submit application forms seeking permission for holding pujas at their local police stations by October 7.        
	Pandal doors should be 12ftx14ft to ensure that fire tenders can enter the pandal.         
	Pandals should have a generator and fire-fighting arrangements.         
	Use of loudspeakers inside pandals is allowed only from 7am to 11am and 6pm to 10 pm for making announcements. Sound limiters must be used.         
	CCTV cameras must be installed in pandals .         
	Subscription books should have the seal of the local police station.         
	Dont: Pandals must not be more than 40ft high and organisers should leave 4ft open on all four sides of the pandal.        
	No puja should be inaugurated before October 16.         
	No cooking within 200 yards of a pandal.        
	No loudspeakers within 100 metres of hospitals.        
	No forcible collection of subscription.         
	Mikes or instruments should not be played in the Nimtala ghat area during immersion.        
	No bursting of crackers that cause sound pollution.        
	Those who plan to immerse idols between Bagbazar and Gwalior ghats should not make the deity more than 17ft high to avoid damaging an overhead electric cable.                                                                                                                                                                           
